    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-10-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-10-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="127"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d127">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Jernigan</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Uhl.</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">U. S. Consulate-General</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-10-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 9, 1894</hi>
                        </date>. (Received November 13.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: * * * The two alleged Japanese spies are alive,
                    and have all they need to eat and drink. Many of the reports in the home papers
                    about them are so false as to be past finding out.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">T. R. Jernigan.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
